4914	[Section equivalence for the dual of the unit]
4915	  \label{def:unit_dual_section_equiv}
4916	  \lean{PresheafOfModules.unitDualSectionEquiv}
4917	  \uses{def:eval_lin, def:global_smul, def:presheaf_internal_hom_slice_value}
4918	  For a presheaf of modules over a base ring presheaf \(R_0\) and an object \(X\), the
4919	  \(R_0(X)\)-linear equivalence
4920	  \[
4921	    \bigl(\mathtt{restr}_X\,\mathbf 1 \to \mathtt{restr}_X\,\mathbf 1\bigr)
4922	      \;\simeq_{R_0(X)}\; R_0(X)
4923	  \]
4924	  identifying endomorphisms of the (restricted) monoidal unit with the ground ring, via
4925	  evaluation at the global section \(1\); the inverse is multiplication by a global scalar
4926	  (\cref{def:global_smul}).
4927	\end{definition}
4928	\begin{proof}
4929	  \uses{def:eval_lin, def:global_smul, def:presheaf_internal_hom_slice_value}
4930	  Proved directly in Lean. The forward map is \(\mathtt{evalLin}\) at \(1\)
4931	  (\cref{def:eval_lin}); the inverse is the global-scalar action \(\mathtt{globalSMul}\)
4932	  (\cref{def:global_smul}). The substantive field is \(\mathtt{left\_inv}\): every
4933	  endomorphism of the unit is multiplication by its value at \(1\), which follows from the
4934	  \(\varphi\)-naturality of the section toward the terminal object of the slice. The module
4935	  structure on the hom-space is the slice internal-hom structure
4936	  (\cref{def:presheaf_internal_hom_slice_value}).
4937	\end{proof}
