4973	\begin{lemma}\leanok
4974	[Reverse slice dual transport (the \(\mathtt{invFun}\) of \cref{lem:slice_dual_transport})]
4975	  \label{lem:slice_dual_transport_inv}
4976	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.sliceDualTransportInv}
4977	  \uses{def:dual_unit_ring_swap_hom, lem:image_preimage_of_le, lem:isiso_eps_restrictscalars_appiso_hom, lem:restrictscalars_ringiso_dualequiv, def:presheaf_dual_unit_iso}
4978	  \textit{Source: internal categorical construction; no external reference.}
4979	  In the setting of \cref{lem:slice_dual_transport}, with \(f : Y \hookrightarrow X\) an open
4980	  immersion, \(M \in \Scheme.\mathtt{Modules}\,X\), \(V \subseteq Y\) an open and \(\beta\)
4981	  the open-immersion structure-ring morphism, there is a reverse transport: a dual section
4982	  \(\psi : \mathtt{restr}_V\,((\mathtt{pushforward}\,\beta)\,M.\mathtt{val}) \to
4983	  \mathtt{restr}_V\,\mathbf 1_Y\) over \(\mathtt{Over}\,V\) is sent to an \(X\)-slice dual
4984	  section \(\mathtt{restr}_{fV}\,M.\mathtt{val} \to \mathtt{restr}_{fV}\,\mathbf 1_X\) over
4985	  \(\mathtt{Over}\,(fV)\), where \(fV = f.\mathtt{opensFunctor}(V)\). This is the inverse leg
4986	  of the forward equivalence \cref{lem:slice_dual_transport}.
